<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1507> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1507" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "M. Cornelius Cethegus succeeded L. Cornelius Lentulus Caudinus as pontifex maximus: see 212, Pontifices." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1506> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1506" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Lentulus as Pont. Max. consulted the Pontifices and the people about a ver sacrum in 217 (Liv. 22.10.1). On his election as Pont. Max. in succession to L. Caecilius Metellus in 221, see 221, Pontifices." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1505> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1505" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/3> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 25.2.2." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1276> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1276" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "L. Cornelius Lentulus Caudinus succeeded L. Caecilius Metellus. On Metellus, see Cic. Sen. 30; Val. Max. 8.13.2; Plin. NH 7.139. Lentulus is mentioned as Pont. Max. in 217 (Liv. 22.10.1). See 213." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1215> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1215" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Lutatius died in office (Fast. Cap., Degrassi 44f., 117, 438f.)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1212> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1212" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Fast. Cap. (names entire); Eutrop. 3.2; Chr. 354; Fast. Hyd., and Chr. Pasc. (with Caudinus, the only name reported, corrupted to Claudius); Cassiod.; Zon. 9.18; see Degrassi 44f., 117, 438f. Both campaigned against Gauls and Ligurians (Polyb. 2.21.3-6; Flor. 1.19.5; Eutrop. 3.2; Zon. 8.18)." .
